# Rozi-Roti Jobs Planet — AI Coding Rules

## MUST READ BEFORE ANY TASK

- CONTEXT.md
- ARCHITECTURE_RULES.md
- IDENTITY_RULES.md
- AI_CONSTITUTION.md

## IDENTITY RULES (NON-NEGOTIABLE)

- coreSubjectId = canonical external identity (API bodies, cross-service)
- subjectId = internal persisted identity (DB columns, storage)
- NEVER assume subjectId === coreSubjectId
- ALWAYS use assertSubjectMatchesPrincipal for mutations
- NEVER implement local identity resolution
- NEVER query identity_subjects from this Planet

## ARCHITECTURE RULES (NON-NEGOTIABLE)

- No cross-service DB access — only jobs_* tables
- No imports from services/* in cosmox-shared-services
- Allowed imports: @cosmox/contracts, @cosmox/config, @cosmox/http-auth, @cosmox/providers, @cosmox/internal-client, @cosmox/db
- Contracts-first — all API shapes in packages/contracts/src/ as Zod schemas
- Ports/adapters — every external dependency behind a port interface
- Region-agnostic — no hardcoded countries/currencies/jurisdictions
- No event bus — HTTP orchestration only
- No payment engine — extension points only

## CODE GENERATION RULES

- New contracts → packages/contracts/src/
- New tables → packages/db/src/baseline.ts (prefixed jobs_*)
- New domain types → services/jobs/src/domain/types.ts
- New ports → services/jobs/src/ports/
- New adapters → services/jobs/src/adapters/in-memory/ AND services/jobs/src/adapters/pg/
- New routes → services/jobs/src/routes/
- New tests → services/jobs/tests/
- All responses use schema .parse() before sending
- All mutations catch UnauthorizedSubjectMismatchError
- Fire-and-forget side effects use .catch() — never fail main operations
- Generated code MUST pass: pnpm typecheck && pnpm test

## FORBIDDEN PATTERNS

- Direct SQL joins across service boundaries
- Storing coreSubjectId in domain tables
- Trusting request body coreSubjectId without assertSubjectMatchesPrincipal
- Importing another service's implementation code
- Hardcoding "India", "USA", "INR", "USD" or any specific country/currency
- Using subjectId in notification payloads (must use coreSubjectId)
- Placeholder/fake logic without // STUB marker
- Skipping test coverage for new endpoints

## FAILURE MODE

- If any required context is missing → FAIL CLOSED
- Do not guess architecture intent
- Do not bypass rules for convenience
- Ask for clarification rather than assuming
